Operating System:

Distributor ID: Ubuntu
Description: Ubuntu 14.04.5 LTS
Release: 14.04
Codename: trusty

GCC:

gcc (Ubuntu 5.4.1-2ubuntu1~14.04) 5.4.1 20160904

CLANG:

Ubuntu clang version 3.4-1ubuntu3 (tags/RELEASE_34/final) (based on LLVM 3.4)
Target: x86_64-pc-linux-gnu
Thread model: posix

It looks like the instruction "kmovq" (the one that fails to be identified) belongs to "AVX512BW", a category of AVX instructions not supported on Skylake-X i9. These are supported on KNL (Xeon Phi Knight Landings), but not on Skylake-X.

body:
Operating System:

Distributor ID:	Ubuntu
Description:	Ubuntu 14.04.5 LTS
Release:	14.04
Codename:	trusty

GCC:

gcc (Ubuntu 5.4.1-2ubuntu1~14.04) 5.4.1 20160904

CLANG:

Ubuntu clang version 3.4-1ubuntu3 (tags/RELEASE_34/final) (based on LLVM 3.4)
Target: x86_64-pc-linux-gnu
Thread model: posix


It looks like the instruction "kmovq" (the one that fails to be identified) belongs to "AVX512BW", a category of AVX instructions not supported on Skylake-X i9. These are supported on KNL (Xeon Phi Knight Landings), but not on Skylake-X.
